Class GenericGamesceneAssignment<T extends IGameScene>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.tokelon.toktales.core.game.state.scene.GenericGamesceneAssignment<T>

    T - The scene type.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    IGameSceneAssignment

    public class GenericGamesceneAssignment<T extends IGameScene>
extends Object
implements IGameSceneAssignment
    Implementation of IGameSceneAssignment using TypeToken.
    Bundles a scene and it's type together in a type safe way that respects generic types.

    This class is intended to be instantiated as an anonymous subclass so it keeps it's type information at runtime.

    An example for that (note the curly braces at the end):
    GameSceneAssignmentIGenericGamesceneString assignment = new GameSceneAssignmentIGenericGamesceneString() { };
